  "body": "<!-- This form is for bug reports and feature requests ONLY! \r\n\r\nIf you're looking for help check [Stack Overflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/kubernetes) and the [troubleshooting guide](https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/debug-application-cluster/troubleshooting/).\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n /kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nThe makeMounts function [skips](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/6fcf841d69165d4aa7a4cb630d512a615ba8645d/pkg/kubelet/kubelet_pods.go#L131) adding volumes to the volumes list if the volume doesn't exist or mounter doesn't exist.\r\n\r\nThis is potentially dangerous behavior because an application can write to the mount path (if it already exists in the container image) expecting it to be backed by a persistent volume, but in fact, is only backed by the container rootfs, which is ephemeral.\r\n\r\nWe probably have not seen this issue manifest in the wild because the volume not existing or mounter being nil should never happen, and also the application would probably see a path/file does not exist error first.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nIf we can't mount all of the user's requested volumes into the container, we should fail to start the container.\r\n\r\n/assign\r\n/sig storage node\r\n/cc @kubernetes/sig-storage-bugs @kubernetes/sig-node-bugs \r\n",
